## ğŸ”— Additional Context

This research was conducted as part of graduate studies at BMS College of Engineering (2023-2024) and continued remotely during MS studies at Clemson University (2024-2025). The work demonstrates the practical application of cloud computing, IoT systems, and data analytics to address real-world agricultural challenges.

The progression from single-plant monitoring (2023) to complex aquaponics ecosystems (2026) showcases the scalability of digital twin technology and validates its potential for sustainable agriculture. Future work could explore:
- Machine learning models for predictive crop yield forecasting
- Integration with automated actuators (pumps, heaters, nutrient dispensers)
- Multi-site deployment for comparative ecosystem analysis
- Edge AI processing on Raspberry Pi to reduce cloud dependency

